Updating an Entitlement Process

Entitlement versioning lets you create multiple versions of an entitlement process, even if itâ€™s assigned to active entitlements and support records.

Available in Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with the Service Cloud.

Use entitlement versioning if:

* You want to make several versions of an entitlement process that have minor differences
* You want to update an entitlement process to reflect changes in your business processes

You can create multiple versions of entitlement processes with the same name, differentiating between them with version numbers and notes. When you create a new version, you can change:

* Name
* Description
* Whether the process is active
* Default version status
* Entry criteria
* Exit criteria
* Add notes about the version

On new versions of entitlement processes that are currently in use, you can add new milestones but not edit existing ones. On new versions of unused processes, you can both add new milestones and edit existing ones.

When creating a new version, you can choose to apply it to all entitlements and support records assigned to the previously used version or only to new entitlements and support records. All versions must be the same type: Case or Work Order.
title: Service Cloud Entitlement Process Updates
